avascript">vl['t1_1ycs'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ycs')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ycs" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Cox's theorem seems to reduce the gap between the formal and the informal, by deriving probability theory from axioms that seem easier to informally assess.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ycs"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ycs" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ycs')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ycs" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ycs')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ycs" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1ycs?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ycs" href="#1ybv" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ycs" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ycs')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ycs class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ycs" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ycs" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ycs" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ygg" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ygg" class="parent"><a name="1ygg" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ygg" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ygg" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ygg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 01:41:56PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ygg'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ygg')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ygg" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-au