ent-date">01 May 2010 03:46:47PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y5w'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y5w')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y5w" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y5w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 03:46:47PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y5w'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y5w'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y5w')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y5w" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I've had 2 Japanese cars.  They're reliable; but when something does break, it's often hidden deep inside the engine so you need to have a mechanic pull the engine out and charge you $700 to replace a $10 part.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y5w"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y5w" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y5w')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y5w" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y5w')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y5w" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y5w?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y5w" href="#1y4u" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y5w" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y5w')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y5w class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y5w" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y5w" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y5w" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1z47" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1z47" class="parent"><a name="1z47" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1z47" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1z47" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1z47" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nanani/">Nanani</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 May 2010 04:47:21AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1z47'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1z47')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1z47" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1z47" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nanani/">Nanani</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 May 2010 04:47:21AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1z47'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1z47'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1z47')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1z47" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Is this not true true of  most modern cars, not only Japanese ones?</p>

<p>Decades ago, drivers could and did repair engines themselves, but today's cars require more knowledge, training, and tools than the hobbyist is likely to have.</p>

<p>The expense of repair says little about reliability. Mean time to failure would be better.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1z47"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1z47" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1z47')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1z47" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1z47')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1z47" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1z47?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1z47" href="#1y5w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1z47" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1z47')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1z47 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1z47" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1z47" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1z47" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1z71" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1z71" class="parent"><a name="1z71" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1z71" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1z71" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1z71" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 May 2010 06:24:09PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1z71'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1z71')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1z71" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1z71" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 May 2010 06:24:09PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1z71'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1z71'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1z71')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1z71" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Expected cost per year, including purchase cost, repair cost, and cost of time spent dealing with failures, would be better.</p>

<p>BTW, cars from heavy snow country last somewhere between 2/3 and 1/2 as long as cars down south (no official statistics, just my observation).  This is due to just a few days per year when the roads are salted.  Do the math, and you'll find it's probably cheaper to take leave without pay and stay home from work on days after it snows - even before taking into account the time saved by not working.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1z71"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1z71" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1z71')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1z71" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1z71')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1z71" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1z71?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1z71" href="#1z47" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1z71" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1z71')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1z71 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1z71" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yfz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1yfz" class="parent"><a name="1yfz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1yfz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yfz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1yfz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Liron/">Liron</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 07:48:08AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yfz'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1yfz')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1yfz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1yfz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Liron/">Liron</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 07:48:08AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1yfz'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yfz'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1yfz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1yfz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That is inconsistent with what I imagined the well-known fact of "Japanese reliability" to mean.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1yfz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1yfz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1yfz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1yfz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1yfz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1yfz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1yfz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1yfz" href="#1y5w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1yfz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1yfz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1yfz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1yfz" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y5f" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y5f" class="parent"><a name="1y5f" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y5f" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y5f" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span c