03:48:22PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y5y'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y5y'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y5y')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y5y" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I love this one. I don't really understand why it got downvoted, yet bizarre mystical religious quotes from nutcases in the Ouspensky/Gurdjieff tradition got upvoted...</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y5y"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y5y" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y5y')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y5y" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y5y')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y5y" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y5y?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y5y" href="#1y5f" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y5y" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y5y')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y5y class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y5y" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y5y" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y5y" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y6l" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y6l" class="parent"><a name="1y6l" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y6l" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y6l" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y6l" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 05:31:28PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y6l'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y6l')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y6l" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y6l" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 05:31:28PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y6l'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y6l'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y6l')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y6l" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I have many questions.</p>

<p>Would you have balked at the idea that we are all, metaphorically, in prison and must seek above all else to escape, if I had quoted a known rationalist?</p>

<p>Do you rate any differently the idea that the task is to understand things so completely that the single right course of action is unmistakable, now that Yvain has quoted Eliezer to that same effect?</p>

<p>Do you think the context of a horror story confers a better aura of rationality on Rain's quote?</p>

<p>Why do you love the idea that we are all insane homicidal maniacs, and dislike <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2c/a_sense_that_more_is_possible/">the idea that there is a way to follow</a>, whether we like it or not, and that the fundamental question in life is whether one makes the only possible choice, or turns away from it? Is your response entangled with whether these things are true or false?</p>

<p>When Eliezer appears to you in a clown suit, will you laugh and turn away?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y6l"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y6l" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y6l')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y6l" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y6l')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y6l" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y6l?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y6l" href="#1y5y" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y6l" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y6l')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y6l class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y6l" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y6l" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y6l" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y76" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y76" class="parent"><a name="1y76" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y76" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y76" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y76" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 07:03:17PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y76'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y76')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y76" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y76" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 07:03:17PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y76'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y76'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y76')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y76" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>When Eliezer appears to you in a clown suit, will you laugh and turn away?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Taken in the context of a general probe attack, this attempt at humor seems out of place.</p>

<p>Probe attack... yes, that's one reason I find quite a few of the questioning responses here agitating or frustrating. Just like a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Port_scanner#Ethics" rel="nofollow">port scan</a>, they have all the patterns of an attack, are used to discover weaknesses and flaws, and can be generally invasive and exhaustingly thorough, even though they're part of the standard toolkit and even more often used for troubleshooting. Enlightenment++</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y76"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y76" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y76')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y76" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y76')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y76" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y76?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y76" href="#1y6l" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y76" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y76')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y76 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y76" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y76" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y76" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y7f" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y7f" class="parent"><a name="1y7f" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y7f" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y7f" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y7f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 07:30:49PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y7f'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y7f')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y7f" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y7f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 07:30:49PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y7f'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y7f'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y7f')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y7f" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I take your point about a "probe attack" and now I find what I wrote unsatisfactory. I'll try again:</p>

<p>Blueberry loves the idea that we're all insane homicidal maniacs, and doesn't like the other ideas, apparently on the grounds that the latter appear in a religious context. This looks like a classic example of judging the truth by the clothes it appears in.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y7f"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y7f" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y7f')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y7f" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y7f')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y7f" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y7f?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y7f" href="#1y76" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y7f" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y7f')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y7f class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y7f" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y7f" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y7f" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y7w" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y7w" class="parent"><a name="1y7w" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y7w" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y7w" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y7w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 08:59:29PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y7w'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y7w')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y7w" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y7w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 08:59:29PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y7w'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y7w'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y7w')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y7w" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Maybe I should have posted it like this:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>As a species we're <a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=%22people+are+crazy+the+world+is+mad%22+site:lesswrong.com">fundamentally insane</a>. Put more than two of us in a room, we <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/gz/policy_debates_should_not_appear_onesided/">pick sides</a> and start <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/gt/a_fable_of_science_and_politics/">dreaming up reasons</a> to <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/i0/are_your_enemies_innately_evil/">kill one another</a>. Why do you think we invented <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/gw/politics_is_the_mindkiller/">politics</a> and <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/11m/atheism_untheism_antitheism">religion</a>?</p>
</blockquote></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y7w"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y7w" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y7w')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y7w" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y7w')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y7w" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y7w?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y7w" href="#1y7f" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y7w" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y7w')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y7w class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y7w" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y56" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y56" class="parent"><a name="1y56" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y56" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y56" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y56" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 01:21:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y56'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y56')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y56" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y56" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 01:21:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y56'>13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y56'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y56')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y56" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Edit: <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/mx/rationality_quotes_3/">DUPLICATE</a></p>

<blockquote>
  <p>"Then the one called Raltariki is really a demon?" asked Tak.</p>
  
  <p>"Yes—and no," said Yama. "If by 'demon' you mean a malefic, supernatural creature, possessed of great powers, life span, and the ability to temporarily assume virtually any shape—then the answer is no. This is the generally accepted definition, but it is untrue in one respect."</p>
  
  <p>"Oh? And what may that be?"</p>
  
  <p>"It is not a supernatural creature."</p>
  
  <p>"But it is all those other things?"</p>
  
  <p>"Yes."</p>
  
  <p>"Then I fail to see what difference it makes whether it be supernatural or not—so long as it is malefic, possesses great powers and life span and has the ability to change its shape at will."</p>
  
  <p>"Ah, but it makes a great deal of difference, you see. It is the difference between the unknown and the unknowable, between science and fantasy—it is a matter of essence. The four points of the compass be logic, knowledge, wisdom and the unknown. Some bow in that final direction. Others advance upon it. To bow before the one is to lose sight of the three. I may submit to the unknown, but never to the unknowable. The man who bows in that final direction is either a saint or a fool. I have no use for either."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Roger Zelazny, <em>Lord of Light</em>. (h/t <a href="http://zhurnaly.com/cgi-bin/wiki/Science_vs._Fantasy" rel="nofollow">zhurnaly</a>)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y56"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y56" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y56')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y56" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y56')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y56" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y56?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y56" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y56')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y56 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y56" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y56" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y56" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ycp" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ycp" class="parent"><a name="1ycp" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ycp" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ycp" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ycp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JamesPfeiffer/">JamesPfeiffer</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 May 2010 08:40:55PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ycp'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ycp')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ycp" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ycp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JamesPfeiffer/">JamesPfeiffer</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 May 2010 08:40:55PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ycp'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ycp'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ycp')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ycp" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p><a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/mx/rationality_quotes_3/" rel="nofollow">http://lesswrong.com/lw/mx/rationality_quotes_3/</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ycp"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ycp" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ycp')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ycp" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ycp')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ycp" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1ycp?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ycp" href="#1y56" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ycp" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ycp')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ycp class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ycp" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ycp" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ycp" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yct" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1yct" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1yct" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yct" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1yct" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1yct" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1yct" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_26y', ['1yct'], 2)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(3 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1yct"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1yct" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y6b" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y6b" class="parent"><a name="1y6b" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y6b" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y6b" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y6b" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Thomas/">Thomas</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 04:26:54PM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y6b'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y6b')">[+] (24 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y6b" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y6b" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Thomas/">Thomas</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 04:26:54PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y6b'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y6b'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y6b')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y6b" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Q: How much does the smoke weight?</p>

<p>A: Subtract from the weight of the wood that was burned the weight  of the ashes that remain, and you will have the weight of the smoke.</p>

<p>--Immanuel Kant</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y6b"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y6b" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y6b')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y6b" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y6b')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y6b" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y6b?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y6b" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y6b')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y6b class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y6b" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y6b" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y6b" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y7s" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y7s" class="parent"><a name="1y7s" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y7s" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y7s" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y7s" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 08:49:11PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y7s'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y7s')">[+] (23 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y7s" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y7s" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 08:49:11PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y7s'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y7s'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y7s')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y7s" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>He left out the weight of the air...</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y7s"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y7s" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y7s')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y7s" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y7s')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y7s" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y7s?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y7s" href="#1y6b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y7s" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y7s')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y7s class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y7s" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y7s" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y7s" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y8u" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y8u" class="parent"><a name="1y8u" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y8u" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y8u" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y8u" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Thomas/">Thomas</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 10:58:03PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y8u'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y8u')">[+] (21 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y8u" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y8u" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Thomas/">Thomas</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 10:58:03PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y8u'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y8u'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y8u')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y8u" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I agree, of course. But don't be too harsh on Immanuel Kant, who had no knowledge of modern chemistry but was able to understand, that Aristotle was essentially wrong in his views about  "natural places of light things up on the sky and heavy things down here on Earth".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y8u"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y8u" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y8u')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y8u" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y8u')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y8u" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y8u?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y8u" href="#1y7s" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y8u" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y8u')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y8u class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y8u" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y8u" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y8u" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yx3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1yx3" class="parent"><a name="1yx3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1yx3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yx3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1yx3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 May 2010 05:56:35PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yx3'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1yx3')">[+] (17 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1yx3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1yx3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 May 2010 05:56:35PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1yx3'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yx3'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1yx3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1yx3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>People understood that Aristotle's understanding of natural place didn't work long before Kant. As early as the 1300s, Oresme laid out problems with this view. The work of Galileo and others made it clear that it didn't make sense. Newton removed any remaining doubts about this. And Newton died about when Kant was born. That Kant knew that Aristotle was wrong is no credit to Kant.</p>

<p>As to the chemistry matter, I'm not completely sure but I think that idea also was around before Kant. Robert Boyle wrote The Skeptical Chemist about 70 years before Kant was born and he touches on the idea of conservation of mass. Hooke also died before Kant was born and did work involving mass loss in chemical reactions. I don't think this can be substantially credited to Kant either.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1yx3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1yx3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1yx3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1yx3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1yx3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1yx3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1yx3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1yx3" href="#1y8u" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1yx3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1yx3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1yx3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1yx3" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1yx3" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1yx3" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yx6" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1yx6" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1yx6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yx6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1yx6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1yx6" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1yx6" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_26y', ['1yx6'], 4)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(17 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1yx6"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1yx6" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yii" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1yii" class="parent"><a name="1yii" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1yii" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yii" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1yii" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/sketerpot/">sketerpot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 08:24:16PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yii'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1yii')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1yii" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1yii" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/sketerpot/">sketerpot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 08:24:16PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1yii'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yii'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1yii')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1yii" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's a reasonable hypothesis that Kant came up with, but until he's tested it -- or at least <em>thought</em> of a way to test it -- he should have been more tentative about it.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1yii"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1yii" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1yii')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1yii" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1yii')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1yii" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1yii?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1yii" href="#1y8u" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1yii" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1yii')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1yii class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1yii" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1yii" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1yii" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35op" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35op" class="parent"><a name="35op" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35op" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35op" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35op" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/benelliott/">benelliott</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 09:54:17AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35op'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35op')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35op" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35op" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/benelliott/">benelliott</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 09:54:17AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35op'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35op'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35op')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35op" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Really? Why is the fact that you've thought of a way to test something a reason to be more confident of it?</p>

<p>I agree that if he had actually tested it that would have been reason for more confidence, but intention to experiment is not Bayesian evidence.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35op"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35op" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35op')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35op" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35op')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35op" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/35op?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35op" href="#1yii" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35op" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35op')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35op class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35op" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yim" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1yim" class="parent"><a name="1yim" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1yim" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yim" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1yim" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JamesPfeiffer/">JamesPfeiffer</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 08:41:15PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1yim'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1yim')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1yim" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1yim" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JamesPfeiffer/">JamesPfeiffer</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 May 2010 08:41:15PM</span><span class="vo