ent('t1_1y4b')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y4b" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Science must have originated in the feeling that something was wrong.</p>

<p>-Thomas Carlyle</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y4b"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y4b" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y4b')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y4b" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y4b')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y4b" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y4b?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y4b" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y4b')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y4b class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y4b" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y4b" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y4b" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ybc" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ybc" class="parent"><a name="1ybc" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ybc" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ybc" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ybc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/djcb/">djcb</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 May 2010 11:31:46AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ybc'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ybc')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ybc" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ybc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/djcb/">djcb</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 May 2010 11:31:46AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ybc'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ybc'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ybc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ybc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's a nice quote, but I would rather think that science originated from the fact that people noticed correlations between things, and then some exceptionally bright people noticed increasingly non-obvious correlations, say in medicine or planetary positions.</p>

<p>I can see the 'something is wrong' part in more recent science, i.e., people experimenting, wondering 'hmm, that's funny,.. not what I expected'. Many scientist might discard such findings, but sometimes some lucky soul found something that is both 'wrong' and not an error of measurement, and discover something new.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ybc"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ybc" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ybc')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ybc" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ybc')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ybc" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1ybc?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ybc" href="#1y4b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ybc" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ybc')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ybc class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ybc" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1yc4" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1yc4" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1yc4" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1yc4" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1yc4" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1yc4" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1yc4" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_26y', ['1yc4'], 1)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(1 reply)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1yc4"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1yc4" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y4h" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y4h" class="parent"><a name="1y4h" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y4h" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y4h" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y4h" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 07:59:00AM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y4h'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y4h')">[+] (13 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y4h" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y4h" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 07:59:00AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y4h'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y4h'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y4h')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y4h" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"You pride yourself on freedom of choice. Let me tell you that this very freedom is one of the factors that most confuse and undermine you. It gives you full play for your neuroses, your surface reactions and your aberrations. What you should aim for is freedom <em>from</em> choice! Faced with two possibilities, you spend time and effort to decide which to accept. You review the whole spectrum of political, emotional, social, physical, psychological and physiological conditioning before coming up with the answer which, more often than not, does not even satisfy you then. Do you know, can you comprehend, what freedom it gives you if you have <em>no</em> choice? Do you know what it means to be able to choose so swiftly and surely that to all intents and purposes you <em>have</em> no choice? The choice that you make, your decision, is based on such positive knowledge that the second alternative may as well not exist."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Rafael Lefort, "The Teachers of Gurdjieff", ch. XIV</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y4h"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y4h" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y4h')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y4h" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y4h')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y4h" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y4h?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y4h" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y4h')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y4h class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y4h" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y4h" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y4h" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y5p" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y5p" class="parent"><a name="1y5p" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y5p" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y5p" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y5p" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SarahC/">SarahC</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 03:35:35PM</span><span class="votes " >8 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y5p'] = ['7 points', '8 points', '9 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y5p')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y5p" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y5p" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SarahC/">SarahC</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 03:35:35PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y5p'>8 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y5p'] = ['7 points', '8 points', '9 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y5p')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y5p" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>This reminds me of something I read in C.S. Lewis which is quite rational: the purpose of curiosity is finding answers.  It's not dithering for the sake of dithering, or debate for the sake of debate.  The goal is to find out what the right answer is, as accurately as possible, not to eternally keep all the options open.  That's how I understand the quote.</p>

<p>Of course, real curiosity can <em>look</em> like dithering and endless debate because people are being very careful not to get things wrong.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y5p"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y5p" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y5p')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y5p" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y5p')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y5p" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y5p?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y5p" href="#1y4h" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y5p" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y5p')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y5p class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y5p" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1y61" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1y61" class="parent"><a name="1y61" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1y61" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1y61" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1y61" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 03:57:22PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y61'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1y61')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1y61" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1y61" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 May 2010 03:57:22PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1y61'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1y61'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1y61')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1y61" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Reminds me of something Jesus said: "The truth will set you free."  By which I think he actually meant something very Buddhist, and sinister: Stop being attached to people and things.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1y61"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1y61" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y61')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1y61" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1y61')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1y61" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/26y/rationality_quotes_may_2010/1y61?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1y61" href="#1y4h" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1y61" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1y61')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1y61 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1y61" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1y61" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1y61" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ybo" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ybo" class="parent"><a name="1ybo" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ybo" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ybo" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ybo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cupholder/">cupholder</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 May 2010 03:37:32PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ybo'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ybo')">[+] (0 childre